ALAMO-HUECO RANCH — The boys wake before dawn, eat sausage and biscuits in the cookhouse and saddle their horses at first light.
James Hurt is 12, a month away from becoming a teenager.
They take ranch work seriously and see their future here.
The boys have one of the longest bus commutes to school in the state, nearly two hours each way to and from Animas.
“Probably riding a horse,” James says.